SUMMARY:Healing Arts One-Time Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Healing Arts One-Time Workshop in Davis \nMonday\, May 18\, 10-11:45 AM \n$5 Members\, $10 Non-Members (all materials included) \n  \nPart of the Pence’s Healing Arts Program and run by facilitator Amy Vidra\, this one-time workshop focuses more broadly on themes related to depression\, anxiety\, or major life changes. Through the process of art making\, participants will have opportunities for discussion\, education\, and connecting with peers in a safe and supportive space. \n  \nRegistration is required in advance through our website\, and space is limited to the first 8 participants who register. Participants must be 18 or older\, and no art experience is necessary. This program is generously sponsored by Bob & Joanne Andresen. \n  \nRegister here (REQUIRED): https://pencegallery.org/education/programs/workshops-and-classes/ \n  \n[If you register for this session and are unable to attend\, please let us know in advance.] \n  \nAny questions? Email pencegallery@gmail.com.
URL:https://visitdavis.org/event/healing-arts-one-time-workshop-7/
LOCATION:Pence Gallery\, 212 D Street\, Davis\, CA 95616
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visitdavis.org/wp-content/uploads/Healing_Arts-copy-20-ULgCIn.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Pence Gallery":MAILTO:pencesocialmedia@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
